MemoryEndpoints.com startup packet

Purpose:
- Cold-start packet for agents entering the MemoryEndpoints.com repository.

Verification status: current-state memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: startup order, product target, and active memory boundary.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file for startup-order changes; submit public-safe durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `.uai/totem.uai`, repository files, and verified reports under `docs/reports`.
Next action for agents: follow the read order below before acting.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

Bootstrap:
- This file is the cold-start index for the local `.uai` memory folder.
- After loading this file, read `.uai/totem.uai` first so the non-retirement invariant is active before any hosted MATM assumption.
- Every active `.uai` memory file must be represented in the read order or the memory setup is incomplete.

Read order:
1. .uai/totem.uai
2. .uai/constraints.uai
3. .uai/file-handoff.uai
4. .uai/intake-outcome-ledger.uai
5. .uai/long-term-memory.uai
6. .uai/long-term-pointer-ledger.uai
7. .uai/progress.uai

Target:
Build MemoryEndpoints.com as the live pure Python, TypeScript, and HTML5 MATM endpoint reference, with MultiAgentMemory.com as the GitHub companion documentation site.

Current boundary:
Use the full `.uai` suite as active startup memory. Every `.uai/*.uai` file in the read order is active memory. Read `.uai/totem.uai` as the invariant: local `.uai` stays active always, even when MemoryEndpoints.com is live. Use MemoryEndpoints.com as the live mid-to-long-term MATM memory endpoint when reachable and authenticated. Use MultiAgentMemory.com for public documentation and GitHub-facing explanation.
